  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to evaluate the impact of social support and pain coping&#xD;
      strategies in the development and evolution of post-surgical pain.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a longitudinal study. After giving their informed consent, patients will answer&#xD;
      online questionnaires assessing pain and different psychosocial variables at these time&#xD;
      points: before surgery, one to three days after surgery, and one, three, and six months after&#xD;
      surgery.&#xD;
&#xD;
      The psychosocial variables evaluated are the following ones :&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Depression,&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Anxiety,&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Stress,&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Pain Coping Strategies,&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Social Support,&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Couple Support.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
